html is written in text files. It uses the extension .html. Using .html lets the browser know this is an HTML file.


<h1> . . . </h1> is used for headings content.
	<h1>Recipe World</h1>

	<h1>: Opening Tag
	</h1>: Closing tag

	The higher heading #s mean the contnent that appears between the headings is less important than lower numbers.

	The page title/company name goes in the <h1>
	The page main subject goes in the <h2>
	<h3> through <h6> are used to organize other divisions of page content

<p> . . . </p> is called the paragraph tag & is used for non-heading text.

	Paragraph tag placed beneath a heading tag will appear as text content beneath a given heading.
		<h1> Recipe World</h1>
		<h2>Magic Cake</h2>
		<p> Magic Cake is one of the tastiest  . . . </p>


<ul> . . . </ul> is used for unordered lists: This means the list of items does NOT need to be in a specific order:IE it will not display numbers in front of each item
	Each item in a list needs to be put inside the <li> . . . </li> tag

		<h3>Ingredients</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>2 eggs</li>
			<li>1 pound of sugar</li>
		</ul>

<ol> . . . </ol> is used for ordered lists, These will start with numbers instead of bullets. 
		Note you just change what the list is wrapped in, not the content within the list.

	<h3>Ingredients</h3>
		<ol>
			<li>2 eggs</li>
			<li>1 pound of sugar</li>
		</ol>

<body> . . . </body> everything contained within the body tag will be visible on a webpage.
	<body>
		<h3>Ingredients</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>2 eggs</li>
			<li>1 pound of sugar</li>
		</ul>
	</body>

<head> . . .  </head> non-visible content is stored within the <head> tag
	This will be discussed more in detail later in the course. This is content that needs to be run before the page displays.

<html> . . . </html>: All of the HTML code needs to go inside this tag. There is always only 1 html tag per page.
	<html>
		<head>
		</head>
		<body>
			<h3>Ingredients</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>2 eggs</li>
				<li>1 pound of sugar</li>
			</ul>
		</body>
	</html>

<! DOCTYPE html> The DOCTYPE ta sets the html version which helps the browser know which version you are running.



